Occidental Petroleum Corp. said it bought the phenolic resins business of BTL Specialty Resins Corp., a unit of BTL Industries Inc. Terms weren't disclosed. 

The purchase includes a phenolic resins plant in Niagara Falls, N.Y., with an annual capacity of 50 million pounds.
Phenolic resins, a form of plastics, are used in a variety of automotive and consumer products. 

Occidental Petroleum, based in Los Angeles, said the purchase makes its Occidental Chemical Corp. unit the nation's third-largest phenolic resins producer.
Occidental Petroleum has interests in oil and gas, pipelines, chemicals, and agricultural products.
BTL Industries Inc., based in Burlington, Ont., is a chemicals and plastics concern. 

